Czechs Facing $2.4 Billion in Solar Lawsuits, Hospodarske Says

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-06-14T06:02:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/czechs-facing-2-4-billion-in-solar-lawsuits-hospodarske-says.html
The Czech Republic is facing as much
as 40 billion koruna ($2.4 billion) in claims from investors in
photovoltaic power plants, Hospodarske Noviny  reported , citing
Radek Snabl, an adviser to the  Finance Ministry .  Foreign investors have so far registered 25 billion koruna
in claims that they will seek in international arbitration suits
after the country imposed a new tax on the solar industry, the
Prague-based newspaper reported, citing Snabl.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  